    "body": "###### Reproduction Steps\r\n\r\n1. Open Reviewer screen\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204135695-d8003f6a-bbcc-493c-87ee-500134d410d8.png)\r\n\r\n2. Settings -> General -> Language\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204136342-856f8254-2f5d-4ad1-bf4f-f6118d48c5ba.png)\r\n3. Change the language from the current one to another\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204135549-6771dc79-0610-4e77-9e6e-f3976f67d8f6.png)\r\n\r\n5. Go back to Reviewer screen\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Expected Result\r\nThe string of estimated studying time on App bar is changed from the one of the previous language (e.g. \"1 minute left\") to the one of the current language (e.g. \"1 minute restante\").\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204135619-431c03c5-d0f4-4b3d-8099-eada27bf1549.png)\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Actual Result\r\nThe string isn't changed. It won't until AnkiDroid is restarted.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204135800-34f97899-026f-48f1-b6c3-15be4eab44d3.png)\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/10436072/204135373-7dfbe132-6765-4c38-8dcf-67910dfdf8c9.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Debug info\r\nAnkiDroid Version = 2.16alpha90\r\n\r\nAndroid Version = 11\r\n\r\nManufacturer = OPPO\r\n\r\nModel = CPH2013\r\n\r\nHardware = qcom\r\n\r\nWebview User Agent = Mozilla/5.0 (Linux; Android 11; CPH2013 Build/RKQ1.200903.002; wv) AppleWebKit/537.36 (KHTML, like Gecko) Version/4.0 Chrome/107.0.5304.91 Mobile Safari/537.36\r\n\r\nACRA UUID = 69410480-0b9c-401f-ae8d-94da0f29c9dc\r\n\r\nNew schema = true\r\n\r\nScheduler = std3\r\n\r\nCrash Reports Enabled = true\r\n\r\nDatabaseV2 Enabled = true\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n###### Research\r\n\r\n- [x] I have read the [support page](https://ankidroid.org/docs/help.html) and am reporting a bug or enhancement request specific to AnkiDroid\r\n- [x] I have checked the [manual](https://ankidroid.org/docs/manual.html) and the [FAQ](https://github.com/ankidroid/Anki-Android/wiki/FAQ) and could not find a solution to my issue\r\n- [x] I have searched for similar existing issues here and on the user forum\r\n     This issue is similar to #10772.\r\n- [x] (Optional) I have confirmed the issue is not resolved in the latest alpha release ([instructions](https://docs.ankidroid.org/manual.html#betaTesting))\r\n\r\n\r\n",
